[[{{PAGENAME}}]] is a [[Kofun]] found on the premises of [[Makimuku ruins]]<ref>https://www.rekihaku.ac.jp/english/outline/publication/ronbun/ronbun7/pdf/163004.pdf</ref>.<ref>{{Cite web |title=「纒,向,矢,塚,古墳,まき,むく,づか,奈良,県,桜井,市,群,属する」を使った英語表現・例文・フレーズ｜Cheer up! English |url=http://english.cheerup.jp/corpus/search?name=%E7%BA%92+%E5%90%91+%E7%9F%A2+%E5%A1%9A+%E5%8F%A4%E5%A2%B3+%E3%81%BE%E3%81%8D+%E3%82%80%E3%81%8F+%E3%81%A5%E3%81%8B+%E5%A5%88%E8%89%AF+%E7%9C%8C+%E6%A1%9C%E4%BA%95+%E5%B8%82+%E7%BE%A4+%E5%B1%9E%E3%81%99%E3%82%8B |access-date=2023-10-16 |website=Cheer up! English |language=ja}}</ref>It is a Kofun of [[Makimuku ruins]].<ref>{{Cite book |last=Kidder |first=J. Edward |url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1515/9780824862848 |title=Himiko and Japan's Elusive Chiefdom of Yamatai |date=2017-12-18 |publisher=University of Hawaii Press |isbn=978-0-8248-6284-8}}</ref>{{rp|249}}

{{ill|Higashidaotsuka Kofun|lt=Higaida-ōtsuka Kofun|ja|東田大塚古墳}} is located to the north of it..<ref name=":1">{{Cite book |last=Kidder |first=J. Edward |url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1515/9780824862848 |title=Himiko and Japan's Elusive Chiefdom of Yamatai |date=2017-12-18 |publisher=University of Hawaii Press |isbn=978-0-8248-6284-8}}</ref>{{rp|251}} It's on the northwestern part of the group..<ref name=":1" />{{rp|251}}

